snippet.textDisplay:
Dear everyone else in this comment section: that police officer did not infringe upon his rights. "There are categories of speech that are explicitly not protected. These free speech exceptions may be deceptively easy to tick off on a list, yet confoundingly nuanced in how they are applied. Often, it can come down to interpretation. And despite federal constitutional jurisdiction, states and even local municipalities can have their own spin on what constitutes “disorderly conduct.” Where you are can make all the difference whether you can be legitimately arrested and charged."
You all look like HUGE idiots commenting about how the cop broke the law when you dont actually know the law yourselves. Please know the law before you give your opinion.
